      "role": "user",
      "content": "I've been reading about different legal cases where religious groups try to get exemptions from laws, like healthcare mandates or even certain civil rights rules. In your view, should religious organizations be allowed to opt-out of government mandates that conflict with their beliefs, or does that just undermine the secular nature of the state?",
